== System Requirements Analysis

The system requirements (WP5.4) define nine functional and non-functional groups, validated through a review session. The table maps each group to its architectural driver, hardware/software element, and key SLA.

{table class="wrapped"}
{colgroup}
 {col }
 {col }
 {col }
 {/colgroup}
{tr}
{th}**SR Group**{/th}
{th}**Architectural Driver**{/th}
{th}**Key SLA / Constraint**{/th}
{/tr}
{tr}
{td}SR-1 - Environmental Monitoring{/td}
{td}Polling engine 60 s; SN-3002 (soil 7-in-1) + SHT10 (air) + NDIR (CO2); threshold breach alert 5 s{/td}
{td}Poll: 60 s; Alert: 5 s{/td}
{/tr}
{tr}
{td}SR-2 - Irrigation & Climate{/td}
{td}Irrigation valve, heating/ventilation; PID (temp +/-0.5C) + hysteresis (humidity){/td}
{td}Auto: 30 s; Manual: 10 s{/td}
{/tr}
{tr}
{td}SR-3 - Web Dashboard{/td}
{td}Responsive SPA 360-2560 px; auto-refresh 10 s; staleness warning 60 s{/td}
{td}Refresh: 10 s{/td}
{/tr}
{tr}
{td}SR-4 - Alerts & Notifications{/td}
{td}Two-tier: in-dash 5 s; push/SMS 30 s dispatch after 60 s critical; Heat/Frost label{/td}
{td}In-dash: 5 s; Dispatch: 30 s{/td}
{/tr}
{tr}
{td}SR-5 - Historical Data{/td}
{td}InfluxDB/TimescaleDB 90-day; ISO 8601 timestamps; CSV/XLSX export; trend charts{/td}
{td}Retention: 90 days{/td}
{/tr}
{tr}
{td}SR-6 - Connectivity{/td}
{td}MQTT/TLS 1.2+ QoS 1 over 4G/5G; offline 72 h min; zero-loss sync on reconnect{/td}
{td}Offline: 72 h min{/td}
{/tr}
{tr}
{td}SR-7 - Affordability{/td}
{td}Hardware BOM 2000 EUR max; resource logging per event with trigger type{/td}
{td}BOM: 2000 EUR{/td}
{/tr}
{tr}
{td}SR-8 - Multi-Site{/td}
{td}Unified dashboard 10 sites; initial load 5 s; auto-refresh 3 s over 4G/5G{/td}
{td}Load: 5 s; Refresh: 3 s{/td}
{/tr}
{tr}
{td}SR-9 - Cybersecurity{/td}
{td}TLS 1.2+/X.509 mTLS; RBAC Operator/Viewer; HTTP 401/403; audit log; offline auth{/td}
{td}All MQTT: TLS 1.2+{/td}
{/tr}
{/table}

== High-Level Architectural Design

The GMS architecture follows a five-layer modular design. Hardware is confirmed in WP6.2: Arduino Portenta Machine Control (STM32H747 dual-core). Cortex-M7 (10 Hz) runs PID/hysteresis control loops; Cortex-M4 handles local LAN MQTT communications. Cloud uses InfluxDB or TimescaleDB for time-series storage.

{table class="wrapped"}
{colgroup}
 {col }
 {col }
 {col }
 {/colgroup}
