=== System Operational Modes

The GMS operates in five modes managed by the Edge Controller System State Controller. Each mode activates/deactivates specific component responsibilities:

{table class="wrapped"}
{colgroup}
 {col }
 {col }
 {col }
 {/colgroup}
{tr}
{th}**Mode**{/th}
{th}**Active Components**{/th}
{th}**Key Static Constraint**{/th}
{/tr}
{tr}
{td}Normal Operation{/td}
{td}All components; Sensor Acq -> Automation -> Cloud -> Dashboard{/td}
{td}MQTT QoS 1; TLS 1.2+; polling 60 s{/td}
{/tr}
{tr}
{td}Offline Autonomous{/td}
{td}Sensor Acq + Local Automation Engine + Offline Buffer only (edge){/td}
{td}Min 72 h; no cloud for actuation{/td}
{/tr}
{tr}
{td}Manual Override{/td}
{td}Local Automation (automation paused per-actuator); REST API -> IrrigationController{/td}
{td}Safety interlocks always active; audit log required{/td}
{/tr}
{tr}
{td}Configuration{/td}
{td}ThresholdConfigStore + ScheduleExecutor; propagate to Cortex-M7 within 60 s{/td}
{td}Persists across restart; applies immediately{/td}
{/tr}
{tr}
{td}Emergency Stop{/td}
{td}ActuatorSafetyInterlock (all -> safe state); AlertService -> push/SMS{/td}
{td}Completes within 60 s; manual ACK to resume{/td}
{/tr}
{/table}

