== Component Details and Interfaces

=== Sensor Acquisition & Environmental Monitoring System

{table class="wrapped"}
{colgroup}
 {col }
 {col }
 {/colgroup}
{tr}
{td}**Architectural Element**{/td}
{td}Sensor Acquisition & Environmental Monitoring System{/td}
{/tr}
{tr}
{td}**Component Type**{/td}
{td}Perception Subsystem{/td}
{/tr}
{tr}
{td}**Responsible**{/td}
{td}Cojocaru Daniel{/td}
{/tr}
{tr}
{td}**Platform**{/td}
{td}STM32H747 Cortex-M7 Core; RS-485 Modbus RTU (SN-3002-TR-ECTHNPKPH-N01), 2-wire Serial (SHT10), UART/Modbus RTU (NDIR CO2){/td}
{/tr}
{tr}
{td}**Purpose**{/td}
{td}Continuously reads soil moisture, soil temperature, EC, pH, N, P, K (SN-3002-TR-ECTHNPKPH-N01), air temperature and relative humidity (SHT10), and CO2 concentration (NDIR) at 60 s intervals and transmits to cloud (SR-1.1). Evaluates against operator-configured thresholds and generates alert events within 5 s (SR-1.2). Light intensity (PAR/BH1750) excluded from pilot scope (review R4).{/td}
{/tr}
{tr}
{td}**Scope**{/td}
{td}Sensor polling, 3-stage validation (range/plausibility/rate-of-change), threshold evaluation, alert classification, data serialisation, local MQTT payload preparation, fault counter monitoring{/td}
{/tr}
{tr}
{td}**Key Features**{/td}
{td}{ul}

- Polls 4 parameters at 60 s intervals - deterministic on Cortex-M7 (SR-1.1)
- 3-stage validation: range check, plausibility, rate-of-change guard (e.g. rejects implausible EC or temperature jumps between cycles)
- Threshold breach alert event generation 5 s SLA (SR-1.2)
- Temperature auto-actuation within 30 s: heating at <10C, ventilation at >35C; operator-configurable defaults (SR-1.3)
- Humidity ventilation within 30 s of exceeding maximum configured threshold (SR-1.4)
- CO2 informational advisory when concentration drops below 800 ppm (SR-1.5)
- SensorFaultMonitor: configurable fault counter per sensor; flags alarm on persistent failures
- MQTT publish is non-blocking - local MQTT outage does not delay local threshold evaluation
- Light intensity excluded from pilot scope (no corresponding SHR, review R4)
{/ul}{/td}
{/tr}
{/table}

