=== Mini PC Edge Gateway

{table class="wrapped"}
{colgroup}
 {col }
 {col }
 {/colgroup}
{tr}
{td}**Architectural Element**{/td}
{td}Mini PC Edge Gateway{/td}
{/tr}
{tr}
{td}**Component Type**{/td}
{td}Gateway Subsystem{/td}
{/tr}
{tr}
{td}**Responsible**{/td}
{td}Alexei Maxim{/td}
{/tr}
{tr}
{td}**Platform**{/td}
{td}Linux OS; Local MQTT Broker (Mosquitto); Python/Node.js for Decision Engine{/td}
{/tr}
{tr}
{td}**Purpose**{/td}
{td}Acts as the central integration point for all greenhouse zones, maintaining a local MQTT broker, executing cached AI logic during cloud outages, and buffering telemetry to guarantee zero data loss over unstable WAN connections.{/td}
{/tr}
{tr}
{td}**Scope**{/td}
{td}Local MQTT aggregation, multi-zone coordination, offline telemetry buffer (72 h+), cached AI parameter execution, X.509 mTLS WAN boundary{/td}
{/tr}
{tr}
{td}**Key Features**{/td}
{td}{ul}

- Operates a local LAN MQTT broker (Mosquitto) for fast, lightweight communication with all zone controllers
- Buffers up to 72 hours of telemetry from all zones during WAN outages
- Executes cached AI-derived setpoints and cross-zone arbitration rules
- Serves as the sole WAN boundary, maintaining a single X.509 mutual TLS connection to the cloud EMQX broker
- Flushes buffered records in batches upon cloud reconnection, ensuring zero data loss (SR-6.2)
{/ul}{/td}
{/tr}
{/table}

