=== Cybersecurity System

{table class="wrapped"}
{colgroup}
 {col }
 {col }
 {/colgroup}
{tr}
{td}**Architectural Element**{/td}
{td}Cybersecurity System{/td}
{/tr}
{tr}
{td}**Component Type**{/td}
{td}Cross-Cutting Security Subsystem{/td}
{/tr}
{tr}
{td}**Responsible**{/td}
{td}Vremere Adrian{/td}
{/tr}
{tr}
{td}**Platform**{/td}
{td}TLS termination at MQTT broker and REST API Gateway; JWT for web auth; X.509 CertificateStore on edge controller (Cortex-M4); EdgeAuthModule independent of cloud{/td}
{/tr}
{tr}
{td}**Purpose**{/td}
{td}End-to-end security across all GMS layers: encrypted edge-to-cloud communication, RBAC on the web dashboard, audit logging of all access attempts, and offline authentication enforcement on the edge controller.{/td}
{/tr}
{tr}
{td}**Scope**{/td}
{td}TLS 1.2+ termination with X.509 client cert validation (MQTT); JWT RBAC (REST API); user account management; request guard HTTP 401/403; append-only audit log with IP and timestamp; offline local auth (edge){/td}
{/tr}
{tr}
{td}**Key Features**{/td}
{td}{ul}

- All MQTT communication: TLS 1.2+; edge authenticates with X.509 client certificate (SR-9.1)
- RBAC: Operator (full read/write, account management) and Viewer (read-only) (SR-9.2)
- Operator creates, modifies, deactivates user accounts; initial Operator provisioned at installation (SR-9.2, review R7)
- All unauthenticated/unauthorised API requests: HTTP 401/403, logged with timestamp and source IP (SR-9.3)
- EdgeAuthModule: WAN offline mode enforces pre-provisioned credential auth on Mini PC; operates without cloud (SR-9.4)
- CertificateStore: manages X.509 edge certs; supports certificate rotation
- MQTT QoS 1 prevents command injection on unstable 4G/5G; TLS prevents eavesdropping and replay
{/ul}{/td}
{/tr}
{/table}

{image file="cybersecurity_component.png" width=749}

==== Component Interfaces

{table class="wrapped"}
{colgroup}
 {col }
 {col }
 {col }
 {/colgroup}
{tr}
{th}**Interface**{/th}
{th}**Description / Scope**{/th}
{th}**Connected Component**{/th}
{/tr}
{tr}
{td}**SEC-MQTT-IF**{/td}
{td}X.509 mutual TLS interface between TLSTerminationModule and MQTT Broker. Broker rejects connections without valid pre-provisioned cert. All traffic TLS 1.2+ minimum. Applies to all sensor data and actuator command messages (SR-9.1).{/td}
{td}MQTT Broker (Cloud Backend){/td}
{/tr}
{tr}
{td}**SEC-API-IF**{/td}
{td}JWT validation and RBAC by RequestGuard before every REST API endpoint. Returns HTTP 401 (no token) or HTTP 403 (wrong role) on failure.{/td}
{td}REST API Gateway (Cloud Backend){/td}
{/tr}
{tr}
{td}**SEC-AUDIT-IF**{/td}
{td}AuditLogger: called by RequestGuard on every rejected request. Persists timestamp, source IP, route, rejection reason to append-only audit trail.{/td}
{td}Audit Log Store (Cloud Backend){/td}
{/tr}
{tr}
{td}**SEC-EDGE-IF**{/td}
{td}EdgeAuthModule on edge local API: validates pre-provisioned credential when cloud unavailable. Returns HTTP 401 if unauthenticated. Fully independent of cloud (SR-9.4).{/td}
{td}Mini PC Gateway Local API{/td}
{/tr}
{tr}
{td}**SEC-USERMGMT-IF**{/td}
{td}UserAccountManager: Operator-only interface to create/modify/deactivate accounts and assign Viewer role. Persisted server-side per user account (SR-9.2).{/td}
{td}AuthN/AuthZ Service / Web Dashboard{/td}
{/tr}
{/table}

{br}

== GMS sequence diagram

The GMS sequence diagram illustrates three key operational scenarios: normal sensor-to-cloud data flow with operator control, autonomous offline operation with local data buffering, and emergency stop with safe shutdown and operator notification. It shows how the five system components: Sensor Acquisition, Local Automation, Cloud Backend, Web Dashboard, and Cybersecurity interact and maintain greenhouse control under both connected and disconnected conditions.

{br}

{image file="MQTT Sensor Data Management-2026-03-22-194459(1).png"}

== Architectural Decisions and Rationale

{table class="wrapped"}
{colgroup}
 {col }
 {col }
 {col }
 {/colgroup}
{tr}
{th}**Decision**{/th}
{th}**Rationale**{/th}
{th}**Requirements / Source**{/th}
{/tr}
{tr}
{td}Mini PC Edge Gateway (5-Layer Architecture){/td}
{td}Reduces N Portenta connections to a single WAN trust boundary. Offloads memory-heavy 72h buffering and complex certificate management from the microcontrollers to a Linux environment.{/td}
{td}SR-6.1, SR-6.2, SR-9.1, Review R1, R2, R4{/td}
{/tr}
{tr}
{td}AI Agent as Backend Client{/td}
{td}Decouples experimental AI logic from deterministic edge control loops. Allows proactive threshold optimization based on historical trends without risking real-time crop safety.{/td}
{td}Review R3{/td}
{/tr}
{tr}
{td}STM32H747 dual-core edge controller{/td}
{td}M7 runs deterministic PID at 10 Hz without OS jitter; M4 handles MQTT/security separately, so comms delays never affect the control loop.{/td}
{td}SR-1.1, SR-2.1,{/td}
{/tr}
{tr}
{td}InfluxDB / TimescaleDB{/td}
{td}Purpose-built time-series stores outperform relational DBs for time-range queries and retention enforcement. Required for 90-day trend visualisation and seasonal ROI analysis.{/td}
{td}SR-5.1, SR-5.2{/td}
{/tr}
{tr}
{td}MQTT QoS 1 over TLS 1.2+{/td}
{td}QoS 1 (at-least-once) prevents data loss on unstable 4G/5G (55.6% of sites mobile-only per WP3.3). TLS 1.2+ prevents command injection and eavesdropping.{/td}
{td}SR-6.1, SR-9.1, WP3.3 survey{/td}
{/tr}
{tr}
{td}PID for temperature, hysteresis for humidity{/td}
{td}PID achieves +/-0.5C setpoint stability in Moldova's -15C to +35C range. Hysteresis is adequate for humidity and avoids oscillation.{/td}
{td}SR-1.3, SR-1.4, WP6.2 Climate section{/td}
{/tr}
{tr}
{td}Edge-first offline architecture 72 h+{/td}
{td}3-month offline operation is a real Moldovan farmer use case (WP3.3). Edge-local automation prevents crop damage during extended cloud outages.{/td}
{td}SR-6.2, SR-2.3, Project Charter O5{/td}
{/tr}
{tr}
{td}RBAC Operator/Viewer roles{/td}
{td}Viewer prevents accidental actuation; Operator includes account management (review R7), avoiding a separate admin tier.{/td}
{td}SR-9.2, review R7{/td}
{/tr}
{tr}
{td}Batch flush on reconnect{/td}
{td}Individual re-publish after long outage exceeds 4G rate limits. Batch insert into InfluxDB is efficient and preserves chronological order.{/td}
{td}SR-6.2, WP6.2 Cloud section{/td}
{/tr}
{tr}
{td}Hardware BOM ceiling 2000 EUR{/td}
{td}Constrains component selection to commodity sensors and a single MCU controller, keeping TCO affordable for small Moldovan farms.{/td}
{td}SR-7.1{/td}
{/tr}
{/table}
